==Spanish==

===Verb form===
'''diga'''

# Present subjunctive third person (or second person formal) singular form of ''[[decir]]''; may it/you say; may it/you tell
# way to say [[Hello]] on the [[telephone]]
#: "Diga." ("Talk"); "Dígame." ("Talk to me.", "Say something to me.")

====Synonyms====
*[[bueno]] (2)

====Etymology====
From Latin ''[[dicat]]'', third person singular present subjunctive active of ''[[dicere]]'', '''say''' or '''tell'''.  The subjunctive (''dicat'', '''may he say''') became the Spanish polite imperative (''diga'', ''diga usted'', '''may your mercy say''').